SIMPLE: suggest
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suggest
<hw>Sug*gest"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Suggested</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Suggesting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>suggestus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>suggerere</ets> to put under,
furnish, suggest; <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>gerere</ets> to carry, to
bring. See <er>Jest</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To introduce
indirectly to the thoughts; to cause to be thought of, usually by the
agency of other objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some ideas . . . are <qex>suggested</qex> to the mind by all the
ways of sensation and reflection.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To propose with difference or modesty; to hint; to
intimate; <as>as, to <ex>suggest</ex> a difficulty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To seduce; to prompt to evil; to tempt.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Knowing that tender youth is soon <qex>suggested</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To inform secretly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To hint; allude to; refer to;
insinuate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suggest</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suggest
<hw>Sug*gest"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make suggestions; to
tempt.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And ever weaker grows through acted crime,⟦br⟧
Or seeming-genial, venial fault,⟦br⟧
Recurring and <qex>suggesting</qex> still.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suggester</ent>⟦br⟧
